I was recently told about an Orthodox monastery with a church that had a water well in the middle... it was 50 meters / 170 ft deep and there was an underground river at its bottom. It was left uncovered, just sitting there during Liturgies, services, etc. Kind of creepy in a way

A child somehow fell in the well during one Sunday Liturgy and drowned, afterwards they ensealed the well, surrounded it with a brick wall and a small roof. They made a water fountain instead of it near the entrance of the church, there are rumours the water heals the sick...

Curious fact: When digging a water well, it was possible to accidentally strike methane, causing the entire thing to explode in a hellish blast. Villagers knew this and performed specific rituals before digging one, asking for safety.

Water wells are a connection between the overworld and the underworld. The chthonic space. Water-well cleaner was one of the manliest/bravest professions back in the day, even more so than a soldier maybe. Many legends of evil crawling up from the depths below, bad tales and rumo
